# Ephemeral logs (keep portal post-round-close logs under results/ though).
# Server startup + Vite HMR noise isn't worth tracking; these patterns reach
# into tmp/ too and that's intentional.
*.log
*.log.err
!results/**/*.log

# tmp/backtests/ and tmp/optimizer/ are fully tracked so teammates can browse
# each other's runs after a pull. Timestamped directory names mean no
# cross-user collisions. Yes, this grows the repo — if it ever becomes a
# problem, prune old runs with a dedicated cleanup commit rather than
# gitignoring them.

tmp/backtests/